verses.text_plain: Then Joseph came and told Pharaoh, and said, My father and my brethren, and their flocks, and their herds, and all that they have, are come out of the land of Canaan; and, behold, they are in the land of Goshen.
verses.verse_html: 1Then Joseph came and told Pharaoh, and said, My father and my brethren, and their flocks, and their herds, and all that they have, are come out of the land of Canaan; and, behold, they are in the land of Goshen.

tokens.text: and all that they have, are come out

verses.text_plain: And he took some of his brethren, even five men, and presented them unto Pharaoh.
verses.verse_html: 2And he took some of his brethren, even five men, and presented them unto Pharaoh.

verses.text_plain: And Pharaoh said unto his brethren, What is your occupation? And they said unto Pharaoh, Thy servants are shepherds, both we, and also our fathers.
verses.verse_html: 3And Pharaoh said unto his brethren, What is your occupation? And they said unto Pharaoh, Thy servants are shepherds, both we, and also our fathers.

verses.text_plain: They said moreover unto Pharaoh, For to sojourn in the land are we come; for thy servants have no pasture for their flocks; for the famine is sore in the land of Canaan: now therefore, we pray thee, let thy servants dwell in the land of Goshen.
verses.verse_html: 4They said moreover unto Pharaoh, For to sojourn in the land are we come; for thy servants have no pasture for their flocks; for the famine is sore in the land of Canaan: now therefore, we pray thee, let thy servants dwell in the land of Goshen.

tokens.text: now therefore, we pray thee, let thy servants

verses.text_plain: And Pharaoh spake unto Joseph, saying, Thy father and thy brethren are come unto thee:
verses.verse_html: 5And Pharaoh spake unto Joseph, saying, Thy father and thy brethren are come unto thee:

verses.text_plain: The land of Egypt is before thee; in the best of the land make thy father and brethren to dwell; in the land of Goshen let them dwell: and if thou knowest any men of activity among them, then make them rulers over my cattle.
verses.verse_html: 6The land of Egypt is before thee; in the best of the land make thy father and brethren to dwell; in the land of Goshen let them dwell: and if thou knowest any men of activity among them, then make them rulers over my cattle.

verses.text_plain: And Joseph brought in Jacob his father, and set him before Pharaoh: and Jacob blessed Pharaoh.
verses.verse_html: 7And Joseph brought in Jacob his father, and set him before Pharaoh: and Jacob blessed Pharaoh.

verses.text_plain: And Pharaoh said unto Jacob, How old art thou?
verses.verse_html:
8And Pharaoh said unto Jacob, How old art thou?
 How: Heb. How many are the days of the years of thy life?

footnotes.body_text: How: Heb. How many are the days of the years of thy life?
footnotes.body_html: How: Heb. How many are the days of the years of thy life?

verses.text_plain: And Jacob said unto Pharaoh, The days of the years of my pilgrimage are an hundred and thirty years: few and evil have the days of the years of my life been, and have not attained unto the days of the years of the life of my fathers in the days of their pilgrimage.
verses.verse_html: 9And Jacob said unto Pharaoh, The days of the years of my pilgrimage are an hundred and thirty years: few and evil have the days of the years of my life been, and have not attained unto the days of the years of the life of my fathers in the days of their pilgrimage.

verses.text_plain: And Jacob blessed Pharaoh, and went out from before Pharaoh.
verses.verse_html: 10And Jacob blessed Pharaoh, and went out from before Pharaoh.

verses.text_plain: And Joseph placed his father and his brethren, and gave them a possession in the land of Egypt, in the best of the land, in the land of Rameses, as Pharaoh had commanded.
verses.verse_html: 11And Joseph placed his father and his brethren, and gave them a possession in the land of Egypt, in the best of the land, in the land of Rameses, as Pharaoh had commanded.

verses.text_plain: And Joseph nourished his father, and his brethren, and all his fathers household, with bread, according to their families.
verses.verse_html:
12And Joseph nourished his father, and his brethren, and all his fathers household, with bread, according to their families.
 according: or, as a little child is nourished: Heb. according to the little ones

footnotes.body_text: according: or, as a little child is nourished: Heb. according to the little ones
footnotes.body_html: according: or, as a little child is nourished: Heb. according to the little ones

verses.text_plain: And there was no bread in all the land; for the famine was very sore, so that the land of Egypt and all the land of Canaan fainted by reason of the famine.
verses.verse_html: 13And there was no bread in all the land; for the famine was very sore, so that the land of Egypt and all the land of Canaan fainted by reason of the famine.

verses.text_plain: And Joseph gathered up all the money that was found in the land of Egypt, and in the land of Canaan, for the corn which they bought: and Joseph brought the money into Pharaohs house.
verses.verse_html: 14And Joseph gathered up all the money that was found in the land of Egypt, and in the land of Canaan, for the corn which they bought: and Joseph brought the money into Pharaohs house.

verses.text_plain: And when money failed in the land of Egypt, and in the land of Canaan, all the Egyptians came unto Joseph, and said, Give us bread: for why should we die in thy presence? for the money faileth.
verses.verse_html: 15And when money failed in the land of Egypt, and in the land of Canaan, all the Egyptians came unto Joseph, and said, Give us bread: for why should we die in thy presence? for the money faileth.

tokens.text: in thy presence? for the money

verses.text_plain: And Joseph said, Give your cattle; and I will give you for your cattle, if money fail.
verses.verse_html: 16And Joseph said, Give your cattle; and I will give you for your cattle, if money fail.

verses.text_plain: And they brought their cattle unto Joseph: and Joseph gave them bread in exchange for horses, and for the flocks, and for the cattle of the herds, and for the asses: and he fed them with bread for all their cattle for that year.
verses.verse_html:
17And they brought their cattle unto Joseph: and Joseph gave them bread in exchange for horses, and for the flocks, and for the cattle of the herds, and for the asses: and he fed them with bread for all their cattle for that year.
 fed: Heb. led them

footnotes.body_html: fed: Heb. led them

verses.text_plain: When that year was ended, they came unto him the second year, and said unto him, We will not hide it from my lord, how that our money is spent; my lord also hath our herds of cattle; there is not ought left in the sight of my lord, but our bodies, and our lands:
verses.verse_html: 18When that year was ended, they came unto him the second year, and said unto him, We will not hide it from my lord, how that our money is spent; my lord also hath our herds of cattle; there is not ought left in the sight of my lord, but our bodies, and our lands:

tokens.text: unto him, We will not hide

verses.text_plain: Wherefore shall we die before thine eyes, both we and our land? buy us and our land for bread, and we and our land will be servants unto Pharaoh: and give us seed, that we may live, and not die, that the land be not desolate.
verses.verse_html: 19Wherefore shall we die before thine eyes, both we and our land? buy us and our land for bread, and we and our land will be servants unto Pharaoh: and give us seed, that we may live, and not die, that the land be not desolate.

verses.text_plain: And Joseph bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh; for the Egyptians sold every man his field, because the famine prevailed over them: so the land became Pharaohs.
verses.verse_html: 20And Joseph bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh; for the Egyptians sold every man his field, because the famine prevailed over them: so the land became Pharaohs.

verses.text_plain: And as for the people, he removed them to cities from one end of the borders of Egypt even to the other end thereof.
verses.verse_html: 21And as for the people, he removed them to cities from one end of the borders of Egypt even to the other end thereof.

verses.text_plain: Only the land of the priests bought he not; for the priests had a portion assigned them of Pharaoh, and did eat their portion which Pharaoh gave them: wherefore they sold not their lands.
verses.verse_html:
22Only the land of the priests bought he not; for the priests had a portion assigned them of Pharaoh, and did eat their portion which Pharaoh gave them: wherefore they sold not their lands.
 priests: or, princes

verses.text_plain: Then Joseph said unto the people, Behold, I have bought you this day and your land for Pharaoh: lo, here is seed for you, and ye shall sow the land.
verses.verse_html: 23Then Joseph said unto the people, Behold, I have bought you this day and your land for Pharaoh: lo, here is seed for you, and ye shall sow the land.

tokens.text: for you, and ye shall sow

verses.text_plain: And it shall come to pass in the increase, that ye shall give the fifth part unto Pharaoh, and four parts shall be your own, for seed of the field, and for your food, and for them of your households, and for food for your little ones.
verses.verse_html: 24And it shall come to pass in the increase, that ye shall give the fifth part unto Pharaoh, and four parts shall be your own, for seed of the field, and for your food, and for them of your households, and for food for your little ones.

tokens.text: And it shall come to pass in the increase
shall be your own, for seed
and for them of your households

verses.text_plain: And they said, Thou hast saved our lives: let us find grace in the sight of my lord, and we will be Pharaohs servants.
verses.verse_html: 25And they said, Thou hast saved our lives: let us find grace in the sight of my lord, and we will be Pharaohs servants.

verses.text_plain: And Joseph made it a law over the land of Egypt unto this day, that Pharaoh should have the fifth part; except the land of the priests only, which became not Pharaohs.
verses.verse_html:
26And Joseph made it a law over the land of Egypt unto this day, that Pharaoh should have the fifth part; except the land of the priests only, which became not Pharaohs.
 priests: or, princes

verses.text_plain: And Israel dwelt in the land of Egypt, in the country of Goshen; and they had possessions therein, and grew, and multiplied exceedingly.
verses.verse_html: 27And Israel dwelt in the land of Egypt, in the country of Goshen; and they had possessions therein, and grew, and multiplied exceedingly.

verses.text_plain: And Jacob lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years: so the whole age of Jacob was an hundred forty and seven years.
verses.verse_html:
28And Jacob lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years: so the whole age of Jacob was an hundred forty and seven years.
 the whole: Heb. the days of the years of his life

footnotes.body_text: the whole: Heb. the days of the years of his life
footnotes.body_html: the whole: Heb. the days of the years of his life

verses.text_plain: And the time drew nigh that Israel must die: and he called his son Joseph, and said unto him, If now I have found grace in thy sight, put, I pray thee, thy hand under my thigh, and deal kindly and truly with me; bury me not, I pray thee, in Egypt:
verses.verse_html: 29And the time drew nigh that Israel must die: and he called his son Joseph, and said unto him, If now I have found grace in thy sight, put, I pray thee, thy hand under my thigh, and deal kindly and truly with me; bury me not, I pray thee, in Egypt:

tokens.text: unto him, If now I have found
me not, I pray thee, in Egypt

verses.text_plain: But I will lie with my fathers, and thou shalt carry me out of Egypt, and bury me in their buryingplace. And he said, I will do as thou hast said.
verses.verse_html: 30But I will lie with my fathers, and thou shalt carry me out of Egypt, and bury me in their buryingplace. And he said, I will do as thou hast said.

verses.text_plain: And he said, Swear unto me. And he sware unto him. And Israel bowed himself upon the beds head.
verses.verse_html: 31And he said, Swear unto me. And he sware unto him. And Israel bowed himself upon the beds head.
